      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just so constant. every single minute. even when i'm busy or distracted, it's right there under the surface. people keep telling me to find new hobbies or go out with friends, but they don't get it. how can i go out when everything i built my life around is just... deleted? it feels like i'm just a ghost in my own life. it would be so much easier if i could just opt out of the struggle. like, if i didn't have to feel this anymore. does that even make sense? to just want the silence?",
